各类在线办公软件存在的弊端难以快速改善进而制约用户黏性的提升疫情影响之下，远程办公短期需求暴发。
The drawbacks of all kinds of on-line office software are difficult to improve quickly and restrict the user viscosity of the upgrade epidemic under the impact of telecommuting short-term demand.
据百度热度指数，远程办公搜索指数今年2月份同比增长491%，环比1月份增长317%。
The telecommuting index rose 491 percent in February from a year earlier and 317 percent from January, according to the Baidu Heat Index.
面对庞大的市场需求，阿里钉钉、腾讯企业微信、华为云WeLink、字节跳动飞书、金山办公等多家办公软件纷纷做出优化或推出免费服务。
Faced with huge market demand, Ali nail nail, Tencent enterprise micro-letter, Huawei Yun WeLink, byte beat fly book, Jinshan Office and many other office software have made optimization or launched free services.
与此同时，资本市场也逆势迎来暴发，远程办公概念股二级市场走势强盛，多家云办公企业如苏州科达、齐心集团、会畅通讯、华平股份等远程概念股均出现涨停。
At the same time, capital markets also ushered in an outbreak of capital markets, telecommuting concept shares of the secondary market is strong, such as Suzhou Koda, Qi Xin Group, will be open, Huaping shares and other remote concept shares rose and fell.
作为“双刃剑”的远程办公，疫情过后能否继续狂奔，在一定程度上取代线下办公？远程办公按下加速键在远程办公领域，目前钉钉一家独大，企业微信紧随追赶，飞书仍有较大差距。
As a "double-edged sword" telecommuting, whether the epidemic can continue to rush after the epidemic, to a certain extent replace offline office? Telecommuting press the accelerator key in the field of telecommuting, currently nailed to a dominant position, enterprises micro-letter close to catch up, there is still a big gap.
极光大数据显示，从1月1日至2月21日，钉钉日活跃用户从2610万升至1.5亿；企业微信从562万升至1374万；飞书从7.95万升至25万；华为在去年底推出的办公应用WeLink从7.65万升至18.3万。
According to Aurora, from January 1 to February 21, the number of active nail-nail users rose from 26.1 million to 150 million; the number of microcredits from 5.62 million to 13.74 million; the number of flying books from 79,500 to 250,000; and WeLink, a Huawei office application launched at the end of last year, rose from 76,500 to 183,000.
在3月2日的苹果App Store中，钉钉位于商务类下载榜第一。
In the Apple App Store on March 2, Nails topped the list of business downloads.
大量用户的涌入导致钉钉、企业微信等被短期巨大流量冲击，出现不同程度的卡顿、拥堵甚至系统瘫痪，厂商随即紧急扩容，需求暴增反向倒逼产品快速升级。
The influx of users led to nail, enterprise micro-letter and other short-term huge flow shocks, the emergence of varying degrees of Carton, congestion and even system paralysis, manufacturers immediately emergency expansion, demand surge reverse reverse force products rapidly upgrade.
2月3日，钉钉通过阿里云紧急扩容1万台服务器后，4日再度扩容1万台云服务器，以应对群直播和语音视频会议的流量洪峰；从1月29日至2月6日，腾讯日均扩容云主机接近1.5万台，8天总共扩容超过10万台，投入的计算资源超过100万核。
On 3 February, after an emergency expansion of 10,000 servers via Ariyun, 10,000 cloud servers were again expanded on 4 days to cope with flood peaks in live and voice videoconferencing; from 29 January to 6 February, Tencent Day grew by an average of nearly 15,000 cloud hosts, with a total capacity of over 100,000 in eight days and over 1 million computing resources.
事实上，在流量红利逐渐见顶的互联网下半场，远程办公产品已成为各巨头涉足To B市场的重要武器。
In fact, in the second half of the Internet, where traffic dividends are peaking, telecommuting products have become an important weapon in the hands of giants in the To B market.
中国银行证券研究院分析师钱劲宇认为，未来企业协同办公云环境竞争日趋激烈，市场规模有望持续增长，企业协作办公有望进入快速发展期。
Qian Jinyu, an analyst at the Bank of China Securities Research Institute, thinks that the future business cooperation office cloud environment will become increasingly competitive, the market size is expected to continue to grow, the enterprise cooperative office is expected to enter a period of rapid development.
据咨询机构Frost&Sullivan预测，2022年中国视频会议市场规模达到445.7亿元。
China's video-conferencing market reached 44.57 billion yuan in 2022, according to consulting firm Frost & amp; amp; amp; Sullivan.
艾媒咨询数据显示，2020年新春复工期间，中国有超过1800万家企业采用了线上远程办公模式，共计超过3亿用户使用远程办公应用。
More than 18 million companies in China adopted the telecommuting model during the resumption of work in the new spring of 2020, according to Aimedia consulting data, with more than 300 million users using telecommuting applications.
在巨大的需求缺口下，除了承担企业社会责任外，远程办公厂商也迎来了加强新用户培育、快速提高市场占有率的机会。
In the huge demand gap, in addition to assuming corporate social responsibility, telecommuters have also welcomed the opportunity to strengthen new user training, rapid increase market share.
复工后的较长一段时间内，钉钉、腾讯会议、企业微信等在苹果App Store排行榜上居于前列。
After the resumption of work for a long time, nail nail, Tencent meeting, enterprise micro-letter and so on in Apple App Store ranking top.
天风证券分析师唐海清认为，本次疫情的影响不仅是短期的板块性催化，更是一次非常好的用户习惯培养机遇期，市场应重视此次事件对行业的长期影响。
Tianfeng Securities analyst Tang Haiqing believes that the impact of the epidemic is not only short-term plate catalytic, but also a very good user habit training opportunities, the market should pay attention to the long-term impact of this event on the industry.
国内的企业SaaS行业一直被市场诟病为付费意愿不足，没有美国成熟的商业环境，整体行业发展相对缓慢。
The SaaS industry in China has been criticized by the market for its lack of willingness to pay, the lack of a mature business environment in the United States and the relatively slow growth of the industry as a whole.
目前各大厂商均在推行免费的体验，SaaS类软件的下载和客户注册量迎来高增，预计后续很多会转化成付费用户，从而加速行业发展。
SaaS-like software downloads and customer registrations are up for grabs, and many more are expected to be converted into paying customers, accelerating industry growth.
疫情缓解后或将回落相比较，美国的远程办公发展非常成熟。
The tele-office development in the United States has matured quite well compared with that in the United States, where the epidemic may recede.
例如Wordpress母公司Automattic是一家全员分布式办公企业，即无固定办公室、全员远程办公，甚至连面试新员工都是远程进行的。
For example, Automattic, Wordpress's parent company, is a distributed office enterprise with no fixed offices, full-time telecommuting, and even interviews new employees remotely.
据前瞻产业研究院引用数据，2017年，美国超过八成企业引入了远程办公制度，有3000万人在家远程办公，占美国工作人口的16%至19%。
In 2017, more than 80% of U.S. businesses introduced telecommuting, with 30 million telecommuting workers, or 16% to 19% of the U.S. work force, according to the Institute for Forward Industries.
至2017年，全世界已有24%的公司，尤其是科技公司采用远程办公方式。
By 2017, 24 per cent of companies worldwide, particularly technology companies, were telecommuting.
到2020年，预计约50%的科技公司将有约29%的员工实现远程办公。
About 50 percent of tech companies are expected to have about 29 percent of their workforce telecommuting by 2020.
据查尔斯研究，自1980年以来，美国经济就业从制造业岗位和生产岗位，向服务业岗位转变。
Since 1980, jobs in the U.S. economy have shifted from manufacturing jobs and manufacturing jobs to service jobs, according to Charles.
在远程办公转变因素中，仅有约2%的增长是由职业转变带来，实际上主要驱动力因素是技术的发展，即企业级技术基础设施。
Of the telecommuting factors, only about 2 per cent of the growth was due to career change, and in fact the main driver was technological development, i.e. enterprise-level technological infrastructure.
微软、IBM、甲骨文、思科、西门子等为企业级技术和服务基础设施打下了坚实基础。
Microsoft, IBM, Oracle, Cisco, Siemens and others have laid a solid foundation for enterprise-class technology and service infrastructure.
近年来，北美的SaaS市场几乎处于井喷的状态，协同办公SaaS公司Slack、视频会议SaaS公司Zoom等纷纷上市，微软Teams等都在蓬勃高速发展。
The SaaS market in North America has boomed in recent years, with companies such as SaaS Slack, videoconferencing SaaS Zoom, and Microsoft Teams and others growing at a brisk pace.
艾媒咨询创始人兼CEO张毅向中国新闻周刊表示，当前企业面临愈发严峻的竞争环境，人力成本持续走高，企业追求效率提升和成本降低，远程办公在一定程度上能满足企业需求，而中国远程办公普及率相对较低，企业协作仍为蓝海市场，面临较大发展机会。
Zhang Yi, founder and CEO of Media Consulting, told China News Weekly that companies are facing an increasingly tough competitive environment, with rising labor costs, companies pursuing efficiency gains and lower costs, and telecommuting to a certain extent to meet business needs.
“但此次在家办公为偶发性事件，属于远程办公被动出圈，是广大企业和员工在疫情影响下的无奈之举，并非是市场进化的表现。
"But working from home is an accident, a passive circle of telecommuting, a helpless move by enterprises and employees under the impact of the epidemic, not a manifestation of market evolution.
”张毅表示，虽然对大多数行业可在线上沟通协作，但最终很多合作和交易都要在线下完成，这是远程办公软件无法改变的事实。
While most industries are able to communicate and collaborate online, in the end a lot of cooperation and transactions are done offline, which is the fact that telecommuting software cannot be changed, says Mr Zhang.
艾媒咨询调查数据显示，超六成用户认为远程办公的优势在于工作地点灵活自由，超五成用户认为远程办公节省了通勤时间与花费，超四成用户表示远程办公依赖软件、易受硬件条件影响，近四成用户认为远程办公使沟通协作受到影响。
More than 60 percent of users think telecommuting has the advantage of flexibility and freedom in the workplace, more than 40 percent believe telecommuting saves commuting time and expense, more than 40 percent say telecommuting is software-dependent and hardware-sensitive, and nearly 40 percent say telecommuting affects communication and collaboration.
在职场人新春居家办公期间使用的沟通工具中，排在前三位的分别是微信、电话、QQ，占比分别为84.2%、46.3%、35.8%。
The top three communication tools used in the new spring home office were micromail, telephone and QQ, accounting for 84.2 percent, 46.3 percent and 35.8 percent, respectively.
“钉钉、飞书等排在其后，用户的习惯尚未养成，各类在线办公软件存在的弊端难以快速改善，进而制约用户黏性的提升。
"Nailing, flying books, and so on, the user's habits have not been formed, all kinds of online office software defects are difficult to improve quickly, and then restrict the improvement of user viscosity.
”张毅向中国新闻周刊表示，预计疫情防控期后，在线办公软件需求将会大幅回落。
Zhang told China News Weekly that demand for online office software was expected to fall sharply after the epidemic prevention and control period.
不过远程办公企业可借此契机提升产品服务能力，让传统企业组织架构、办公模式进行有效转变。
However, telecommuting enterprises can use this opportunity to enhance the capacity of products and services, so that the traditional enterprise organizational structure, office model for effective transformation.
“由于线上办公存在互动性差和消解社会交往意义等缺点，在可预见的未来，线下办公不会完全被线上所取代。
"For the foreseeable future, offline work will not be completely replaced by offline due to such shortcomings as poor interactivity and unravelling the meaning of social interaction.
”上海交通大学中国发展研究院执行院长陆铭向中国新闻周刊表示。
Lu Ming, executive director of the China Development Institute at Shanghai Jiaotong University, told China News Weekly.
陆铭认为，线上办公需将任务交代清楚，业绩以任务完成的数量和质量作为评价标准，而对不容易描述清楚的任务，线上开展则较难。
Lu believes that online office needs to be accountable for its tasks, with performance based on the quantity and quality of tasks accomplished, while for tasks that are not easy to describe clearly, it is more difficult to do online.
此外，社会交往可增进人与人之间的感情和信任，线下互动给员工随机互动创新的可能性，同时可以有现场的监督，给予员工努力工作的压力。
In addition, social interaction can enhance interpersonal feelings and trust, and offline interaction gives employees the possibility of random interaction and innovation, as well as on-site supervision and pressure to work hard.
平安证券分析师闫磊认为，在线办公市场短期火热，但要形成“线上生态”还需时日。
Yan Lei, an analyst at Ping An Securities, says the online office market is hot for a while, but it will take time to form an online ecology.
随着疫情的缓解，在线办公热情将会明显回落，行业需开始思考用户维护问题，其中数据安全、用户习惯维持等都是重要门槛，如何跨越需要长期验证。
As the epidemic subsides, the enthusiasm for online office will fall dramatically, and the industry needs to start thinking about user maintenance, where data security, user habits, and so on are important thresholds that need long-term validation.
